								<h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-8">🌐 webNavigation</h3>
								<p class="text-lg leading-7 text-pretty text-black mt-2">
									The <strong>webNavigation</strong> permission lets the extension know when you're navigating to a new webpage, like clicking a link or typing a new address. It doesn't track your activity or see what you're doing—it simply detects when you're visiting specific websites. If those sites are on the extension's list (like NSFW or private sites), it automatically switches to incognito mode for your privacy.
								</p>

								<h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-8">🔗 tabs</h3>
								<p class="text-lg leading-7 text-pretty text-black mt-2">
									The <strong>tabs</strong> permission allows the extension to interact with the tabs you're currently using. It can detect which tab you're on, retrieve its URL, and perform actions like refreshing the tab, moving it to incognito mode, or opening related tabs. This helps the extension work smoothly with your browsing without interrupting your flow!
								</p>

								<h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-8">💾 storage</h3>
